Tree Improvement : Its Contribution to Sustainable Supply of Quality Wood Required by End- Users
August 18 - 22 , 1997 Quebec City , Quebec , Canada _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _
Call for Papers
An International Workshop on the Genetics of Wood Quality to be held at the 26 th Biannual Meeting of the Canadian Tree Improvement Association ( CTIA ) , Quebec City , August 18 - 22 , 1997 on the theme of Tree Improvement : Its Contribution to Sustainable Supply of Quality Wood Required by End- Users
The CTIA and Forintek Canada Corp . ( Canada 's National Wood Products Research Institute ) will organize an international workshop at the 26 th CTIA Biannual Meeting to be held in Quebec City , Canada , next year . The city is internationally renowned as a centre of forest and wood research , and a major tourist destination in Canada . We are requesting papers dealing with various aspects related to the theme such as : * Wood quality required by end users and its meaning to the tree breeder . * Techniques for the nondestructive evaluation of wood quality . * Wood quality vs . quantity correlations . * Genetic variation and inheritance of wood quality traits . * Juvenile-mature wood transition and juvenile wood . * Maker-aided selection for wood quality traits . * Interrelationships between wood quality characteristics . * Variability of wood quality within a tree . * Natural variation in wood quality . * Relationships between external ( e . g . , taper , knots ) and internal ( e . g . , juvenile wood , wood density ) quality characteristics , and product quality and value . * Genetic improvement toward end-use wood characteristics , product quality and value .
Papers are accepted as either oral or poster presentations . In addition , internationally promonent experts will be invited to give an overview of key subjects in this area , and major issues will be discussed . Papers of both oral and poster presentations will be pusblished together as a special issue of a journal or as Workshop Proceedings in addition to the inclusion of the abstracts in the CTIA Proceedings .
